"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423782","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-02","<p>An Impact Assessment was published when the Legal Aid Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012 received Royal Assent.</p><p>The Ministry of Justice is in the process of considering the way forward in relation to the application to insolvency litigation of the no win no fee reforms in Part 2 of the Act.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","13342 ; 13343 ; 13345","2015-11-02T16:32:07.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423782/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423782/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-26","Insolvency: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on director conduct should the funding of insolvency litigation change under the provisions of the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","13344"
