"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423853","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer given by my hon Friend, the Economic Secretary to the Treasury (Harriett Baldwin) on 2 November 2015.</p><p>Credit unions are a devolved matter in Northern Ireland and responsibility for them rests with the Northern Ireland Department of Enterprise, Trade and Investment.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-11-03T15:36:47.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423853/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423853/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423853/answer",,,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-10-26","Northern Ireland Office: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps she is taking to promote the use of credit unions in the work of her Department; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","13520"
