"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423922","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-05","<p>We are currently analysing the responses to the consultation with the Department forCommunities and Local Government.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-05T16:56:12.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423922/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423922/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423922/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-26","Local Press: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many responses have been received to his Department's consultation on business rate relief for local newspapers; and if he will extend that relief to local magazine publishers.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","13271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423923","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>The Digital Single Market is a stated priority for the Juncker Commission, which could deliver significant gains for both consumers and businesses. As such, Ministers across Government regularly hold discussions in Europe and the UK with our European counterparts on the Digital Single Market including its potential effects on UK’s creative industries and publishers in particular.</p><p>Currently there are no Digital Single Market legislative proposals on the table, but we are encouraging the Commission to ensure that future proposals are carefully assessed to ensure that they do not damage incentives to invest in the production of creative content.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-10-28T17:50:26.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423923/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423923/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423923/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-26","Electronic Publishing: EU Action","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with his European counterparts on the potential effect of the European Commission's Digital Single Market proposals on UK publishers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","13272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423924","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for Sheffield Central on 19 October 2015 to UIN: 10765.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-03T13:35:58.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423924/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423924/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423924/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-26","Commission on Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on what basis the membership of the Independent Commission on Freedom of Information was chosen; and what steps he is taking to ensure that the Commission is approaching the review in a fair, open and balanced manner.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423925","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-03","<p>The independent Commission on Freedom of Information is expected to publish its findings in due course following the close of its Call for Evidence on 20 November.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2015-11-03T13:34:21.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423925/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423925/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423925/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-10-26","Commission on Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he expects the Independent Commission on Freedom of Information to publish its report and recommendations.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","13377"
